<br>
&quot;&quot;Equality&quot; in PvP or any game with HvH is a myth.&quot;<br>
<br>
I said, &quot;To me, Player vs Player has always been about equality. Meaning playing on a level playing field, where each player plays by the same rules.&quot; <br>
<br>
I did not even remotely hint that players are equal in ability in PvP. So no need to even imply that i did so. <br>
<br>
&quot;The &quot;level playing field&quot; is a myth as well.&quot; <br>
<br>
As you admit later, it is not a myth in the context i meant it to be. The rules are same for either player in player-vs-player combat (in my opinion) even if the skill of the players is vastly different. If one player uses different rules and has different goals then the &quot;equality&quot; the phrase PvP implies is not there. <br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;Its my opinion that D&amp;D was not &quot;based&quot; on PvP in any way, shape, or form.<br>
<br>
&quot;Then you must have been playing with yourself....:)&quot;<br>
<br>
No, im just playing the game how it was meant to be played along with others who understood the basic fundamentals of RPing. <br>
<br>
&quot;BTW, being governed by the same set of game rules does not necessarily mean being treated the same under those rules.&quot;<br>
<br>
No, but thats really not relevant to my line of reasoning. Seems a weak excuse in an attempt to justify a weak position. <br>
<br>
D&amp;D is based on Player vs Environment. This environment is created and administered by a DM with a goal of providing entertainment to the Players (and thus indirectly obtaining entertainment for himself). <br>
<br>
In many instances a DM controls NPCs (&lt;--NON PLAYER characters, meaning they are NOT players but rather part of the environment). By this very definition, created by the makers of D&amp;D, this is NOT Player vs Player combat. If any thing, its Player vs Non Player combat.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
