<br>
So?  Are you claiming some sort of disparate treatment by the game server?  Or the hardware perhaps?   Maybe the routers have a little conspiracy going on ... "ah, there's Scirocco's 'fire' packet, why don't I just uhh delay that a bit".  :)<br>
<br>
Meddik says:  <b><i>However, on the other hand, there are those such as myself that really have absolutely no interest in PvP. We will not be happy if we are forced into PvP, or if we will miss large portions of the PvE game by avoiding PvP.</b></i><br>
<br>
But PvP has both direct AND indirect consequences, and you, as the non-PvP player, benefit from the indirect consequences even though you do not engage in PvP.  A PvP environment can promote a stronger sense of community and self-government, encourage roleplaying, and increase customer retention -- aspects of the game that will affect you even if you are never engaged in combat with another player.<br>
<br>
No MMRPG can be complete without PvP, no matter how you look at it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/10/01 10:24:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ah!</span><hr size=1> Badaf, you're still missing the point.  It's Human vs. Human combat.  Or Person vs. Person.<br>
<br>
Or, in the context of the game, Human-Controlled Character vs. Human-Controlled Character.  Call one a &quot;PC&quot; and one an &quot;NPC&quot; if you like, it still doesn't change the fact that they're both controlled by humans.<br>
<br>
Don't get lost in the nomenclature.  <br>
<br>
