BTW, no, that's not particularly what I meant.  I was speaking more generally (and tangentially, unfortunately for this thread) about the issue of &quot;equality.&quot;   Everyone participating in a game should be governed by the rules of the game, correct?   My point is that the rules of a game don't have to treat all participants the same.<br>
<br>
Of course, many games do strive to do so, especially where the game is designed around head-to-head conflict resulting in a winner and a loser.  I suspect that many people think that that is what PvP in a RPG is all about.  It can be, but it doesn't have to be.  But it's understandable, especially if one's only exposure to PvP is in the context of Quake or UO.  <br>
