&quot;Actually, it was a DELIBERATE choice of terminology. I know that the term &quot;PvP&quot; pushes buttons and strikes raw nerves. My goal was to challenge exactly those people that DO have that reaction to &quot;PvP,&quot; and consider it synonymous with &quot;PKing.&quot;&quot;<br>
<br>
I take Player versus Player more literally. Meaning a player pitting his skills against another player on a level playing field in an attempt to win by beating the other player as defined by the rules of the game and/or environment.<br>
<br>
David vs Goliath<br>
Packers vs the Rams. <br>
Ali vs Frasier<br>
etc... <br>
<br>
This is how the term PvP was first presented to me and still continues to be defined by the general public today. Your definition of PvP is not the norm and does not carry much weight as far as i see it. <br>
<br>
Therefore, by the way i choose to define what Player vs Player means and how i choose to view the DM/Player relationship in PnP RPGs, they are totally different things. You can continue to argue all you want, but you are not going to change the way i choose to define these things (which is the general public's definition as well). <br>
