Founder, <A HREF=http://pub58.ezboard.com/baodoctors>AO Doctors</A> Message Board.</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=badaf>Badaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/11/01 10:43:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>  re</span><hr size=1> Scirocco<br>
<br>
&quot;Not really. Just trying to help them pierce through all the baggage attached to the term &quot;PvP&quot; to see what truly underlies it. And why people find it objectionable. Which is HvH. Which is also the core of P&amp;P RPGs, where it is usually not objectionable.&quot;<br>
<br>
Once again, i strongly disagree that HvH is the core of PnP RPGs in the context of players and DMs. If a DM was truely &quot;vs&quot; the players, the players would never win. The &quot;core&quot; can not be so narrowly defined to only look to the player vs npc combat, in my opinion. <br>
<br>
&quot;And then, after making the realization that HvH doesn't have to be bad (and, in fact, is often essential to a good story or game), coming back to think anew about how HvH can be incorporated into MMORPGs in a good way.&quot;<br>
<br>
Its not essential to a good story or game. How can i, as a D&amp;D DM, have created enjoyable adventures where there was no player vs DM-controlled characters? <br>
<br>
&quot;If you have a strong adverse reaction to &quot;PvP&quot; in MMORPGs, ask yourself why. And why don't you have the same reaction to PvE?&quot; <br>
<br>
Now THIS is something i can sink my teeth into. <br>
<br>
Game mechanics are a big part of it to me. RPGs, to me, are about character development which usually revolves around character attributes and improvement. These define the character's abilities as he/she interacts with the environment. In a PvP MMOL atmosphere, many of these elements are tossed right out the window. A character's dexterity and agility are, for all intensive purposes, deleted and replaced by the human player's dexterity and agility. In combat, a character's intelligence and wisdom means nothing since that dim witted orge is going to enter combat with all the facilites of a harden Q2 veteran with a blazing connection speed to match. Yea, thats SO immersive. How can someone not have fun roleplaying in that climate? Forget it. <br>
<br>
Have you ever seen melee characters fight each other in a MMOL environment like EQ? Its really quite a sad sight to me. It boils down to having little to do with the character's abilities, mainly relying in the person controlling the characters reaction speed and hand-eye-coordination. Not to mention that if your connection is better than the other guys, your character is better at PvP combat. Yet another example of how game mechanics in the MMOL genre dismiss character development out of hand. <br>
<br>
Another area that causes me pause in PvP MMOLRPG is accountability for ones actions. Im sure someone will come back with the old &quot;well gather up a bunch of people and go get vengence!&quot;. Frankly, i dont buy that. The environment should react to out-of-alignment actions like in a PnP RPG. This is one area i think MMOLRPGs can improve on however. I think Horizons, for example, is finally taking this seriously. I won't go into the mechanics of what they are implimenting here. I have a feeling you know a bit about it already Scirocco since HZ seems to be the first game that might actually get PvP &quot;right&quot; to a large extent. <br>
<br>
Personally, i have never been one to tag PvP in a MMOL setting as something to be avoided. I will be the first to shout that it has not been done even remotely close to my satisfaction....yet. Some day a game might come along that give me the right combination of PvP and Roleplaying that i will find extremely enjoyable. I wont be so jaded as to dismiss it out of hand. But i think that time is still aways off. While player and environment differences that exist outside the game still are there and have such a major impact, i dont see how i will be truely satisfied with a PvP MMOLRPG. It simply takes the character out of the equation which is something i feel is vital to an RPG. <br>
